    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix IPv6 Address Formatting in NAS Data Display Functions\n\n### Summary\nThe NAS data display functions in the AS simulator contained inconsistent IPv6 address formatting that led to incorrectly formatted output when displaying PDN addresses. When `pdnAddress()` was called with `PDN_VALUE_TYPE_IPV4V6`, the resulting string representation would show IPv6 bytes with mixed formatting - some bytes displayed as single hexadecimal digits and others with leading zeros.\n\nThis inconsistency occurred due to a copy-paste error where the format strings in `ipv6Addr()` and `ipv4v6Addr()` used a mix of `%x` and `%.2x` specifiers instead of consistent `%02x` formatting. The issue became apparent when examining NAS trace outputs where IPv6 addresses appeared malformed.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/TEST/AS_SIMULATOR/nas_data.c`: Updated format strings in `ipv6Addr()` and `ipv4v6Addr()` functions to use consistent `%02x` format specifiers for all IPv6 bytes\n- Modified IPv6 format from `\"%x%.2x:%x%.2x:%x%.2x:%x%.2x\"` to `\"%02x%02x:%02x%02x:%02x%02x:%02x%02x\"`\n- Updated IPv4v6 format from `\"%u.%u.%u.%u / %x%.2x:%x%.2x:%x%.2x:%x%.2x\"` to `\"%u.%u.%u.%u / %02x%02x:%02x%02x:%02x%02x:%02x%02x\"`\n\n"
}